                        <h1>(Xiao)Lynn Zhen 17 Years Old October 2018
                            Homeland Chinatown</h1>
                        <div class="en">
                            <p>In the bustling and prosperous metropolis of Chicago, there is a place filled with history and ancient architectures - Chinatown. There are four landmark buildings in Chinatown, including the tianxia plaque, the Kowloon wall, the Pui Tak Center building, and the twelve Chinese zodiac Chinatown square. These buildings, carved beams, and painted buildings are brightly colored, fully reflecting the characteristics of Chinese architecture. The residents of Chinatown come from all parts of the country and have their own local dialect. Mandarin and Cantonese are the most representative languages in Chinatown.  Chinatown is a warm haven, it can let us oversea travelers together feel the warmth of home, and I am one of the beneficiaries.</p>

                            <p>My hometown is Taishan, Guangdong, China. I remember when I first came to the country, Chinatown was so foreign to me, whether it was the environment, the language, or the local customs that would make me feel new and uncomfortable. One of the things that frustrate me the most is the language barrier. My English foundation is not very good. Whenever the English teacher gives us homework, I find it very difficult. I have to translate what I think into English again, and it is a challenge for me. At that time, I did not understand many English vocabularies, and I used mobile translation software to help me. However, the translations from the software weren’t exactly right. I can only write down the general meaning, but the English teacher could not understand what I wrote. He pointed out a lot of mistakes and asked me to revise them and turned in again. I was very frustrated and get stressed out.</p>

                            <p>Fortunately, under a coincidence, I learned that the Pui Tak center could provide after-school tutoring classes for new youth immigrants. I was holding my expectation and walked into the Pui Tak Center. At first, I felt very strange in this new environment, and I was also very introverted. But the teachers in Pui Tak Center are very approachable and kind. They are passionate and dedicated to education. They are respectful and attentive to the suggestions given by the students, and they will try their best to give the students a perfect answer. They are like a group of good teachers and helpful friends, under their guidance, my personality became more cheerful, and gradually get along with my classmates. I have also made progress in learning. Every time when I asked questions about English homework that I did not understand, they patiently taught me and carefully listed the steps to solve the problems, and then taught me step by step until I learned it. As I learned more English vocabularies, I no longer felt distressed when my English teacher assigned homework. Ultimately, I found the right direction and could write out my own ideas. Gradually, I got rid of the help of mobile translation software.</p>

                            <p>Chinatown is like a home, and it makes me feel comfortable and safe. It brought me a lot of unforgettable and beautiful memories, deep in my head, in a place that's important to me.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="zh_HANS">
